========================================================================================================================
READING THIS
========================================================================================================================
• 'seed/soft'    = cash at EACH of 4 softs at the start; sum of 4 + 'unlim' = total bankroll.
• 'transfers'    = total bookkeeping events (arb-out + refill-in) over 180 days.
• '/month'       = transfers expressed as a monthly cadence — the convenience cost.
• '$ arbed'      = total dollars swept from softs → unlimited over 180 days.
• '$ refilled'   = total dollars sent from unlimited → softs to keep bets coverable.
• 'growth'       = pool terminal / start. Same across seed levels (sizing is pool-based).

Sweet spot: smallest seed% where transfers/month feels acceptable AND no row above it
shows a 10× jump in transfer count. Larger seed = fewer transfers but more cash exposed at softs.
